<ContentPage xmlns="http://xamarin.com/schemas/2014/forms"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="Stanmore_App.English"
             BackgroundImageSource="EnglishBackground">
    
    <ContentPage.Content>
        
        <ScrollView VerticalOptions="FillAndExpand" TranslationY="0" >
            <StackLayout HeightRequest="2500" BackgroundColor="Transparent">

                <Image Source="College_logo" HeightRequest="50" TranslationX="-50" TranslationY="0"/>

                <!-- English title -->

                <Label Text="English"  FontSize="20" TextColor="White" HorizontalOptions="Center"></Label>

                <!-- Information to be displayed -->

                <Label Padding="20,20,10,0" FontSize="20" TextColor="LightSeaGreen">

                    <Label.Text>

                        Course Content
Our new ESOL PLUS study programme will give you a great chance to continue to improve your English. ESOL means English for Speakers of Other Languages and the qualification is designed to help you develop the skills you use every day and help you move on to further study.

Course Outcomes
As well as English, you will also improve your Maths and study some other topics which will include Business.

There will also be work experience, trips to related companies or exhibitions and special events.

Progression
Get on a full time course next September
Get part time or full time employment or apprenticeship
Talk to teachers, employers and officials and understand the customs of the UK
Entry Requirements
Aged between 16 and 18 years
Not currently studying
Need to improve your English so you can start a full-time course or get onto an apprenticeship.
 
Assessment
You will have exams and gain a recognised qualification from the English Speaking Board (ESB).

Equipment
N/A

                    </Label.Text>
                </Label>
            </StackLayout>
        </ScrollView>
    </ContentPage.Content>
</ContentPage>